sentences: Stephen West (born December 8, 1966) is an American rock musician, best known for being the drummer for Pavement.
A native of Richmond, Virginia, West went to high school with future Pavement bandmate Bob Nastanovich; the two first met when West was fourteen years old.:
One of his coworkers at the Whitney was Stephen Malkmus, another of his future bandmates in Pavement.
West was tapped to join Pavement in 1993, after the band dismissed their original drummer, Gary Young.
West's first performance with the band was on their 1994 album Crooked Rain, Crooked Rain; he remained in the band until they broke up in 1999.
